SENATE BILL 904
F1 6lr3485
CF HB 1254
By: Senators Zucker, Brooks, and King
Introduced and read first time: February 6, 2026
Assigned to: Education, Energy, and the Environment
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Education – Public Schools – Service Contracts and Professional Development
3 FOR the purpose of requiring a county board of education that seeks to enter into a service
4 contract to submit to the State Department of Education certain information to
5 justify the need for the service contract, and to submit a certain plan of assistance
6 for employees adversely affected by the service contract; requiring, on or before a
7 certain date, the Department to design and develop a new system of professional
8 development for paraeducators and other education support professionals; requiring,
9 on or before a certain date, each county board to provide the new system of
10 professional development to each paraeducator and education support professional
11 employed in a public school in the county; and generally relating to public school
12 service contracts and professional development.
13 BY adding to
14 Article – Education
15 Section 6–132 and 6–133
16 Annotated Code of Maryland
17 (2025 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
18 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
19 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
20 Article – Education
21 6–132.
22 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “SERVICE CONTRACT” MEANS A PROCUREMENT
23 CONTRACT FOR SERVICES THAT WILL BE PROVIDED TO A PUBLIC SCHOOL.
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from exist in g l aw . *sb0904*

2 SENATE BILL 904
1 (B) A COUNTY BOARD THAT SEEKS TO ENTER INTO A SERVICE CONTRACT
2 SHALL SUBMIT TO THE DEPARTMENT THE INFORMATION REQUIRED UNDER THIS
3 SECTION.
4 (C) THE COUNTY BOARD SHALL SUBMIT A DEMONSTRATION THAT THE
5 COUNTY BOARD HAS TAKEN FORMAL AND POSITIVE STEPS TO CONSIDER
6 ALTERNATIVES TO THE SERVICE CONTRACT, INCLUDING REORGANIZATION AND
7 REEVALUATION OF SERVICES AND PERFORMANCE.
8 (D) (1) THE COUNTY BOARD SHALL SUBMIT CALCULATIONS THAT:
9 (I) COMPARE THE COST OF THE SERVICE CONTRACT WITH THE
10 COST OF USING SCHOOL EMPLOYEES; AND
11 (II) SHOW THE SAVINGS TO THE LOCAL SCHOOL SYSTEM, OVER
12 THE DURATION OF THE SERVICE CONTRACT, OF AT LEAST 20% OF THE CONTRACT,
13 EXCLUSIVE OF ANY SAVINGS ATTRIBUTABLE TO A REDUCTION IN EMPLOYEE PAY OR
14 FRINGE BENEFITS.
15 (2) IN CALCULATING THE COST COMPARISON REQUIRED UNDER THIS
16 SUBSECTION, THE COUNTY BOARD SHALL INCLUDE:
17 (I) DIRECT COSTS, INCLUDING FRINGE BENEFITS;
18 (II) INDIRECT OVERHEAD COSTS, INCLUDING THE
19 PROPORTIONAL SHARE OF EXISTING ADMINISTRATIVE SALARIES AND BENEFITS,
20 RENT, EQUIPMENT COSTS, UTILITIES, AND MATERIALS, BUT ONLY TO THE EXTENT
21 THAT THOSE COSTS:
22 1. ARE ATTRIBUTABLE SOLELY TO THE SERVICE IN
23 QUESTION; AND
24 2. WOULD NOT EXIST IF THE SERVICES WERE NOT
25 PERFORMED BY SCHOOL EMPLOYEES;
26 (III) ANY CONTINUING OR TRANSITIONAL COSTS THAT WOULD
27 BE DIRECTLY ASSOCIATED WITH CONTRACTING FOR THE SERVICES, INCLUDING
28 UNEMPLOYMENT COMPENSATION AND THE COST OF TRANSITIONAL SERVICES; AND
29 (IV) ADDITIONAL COSTS OF PERFORMANCE OF SERVICES BY
30 COUNTY BOARD EMPLOYEES, INCLUDING SALARIES AND BENEFITS OF ADDITIONAL
31 STAFF AND THE COST OF ADDITIONAL SPACE, EQUIPMENT, AND MATERIALS NEEDED
32 TO PERFORM THE SERVICES.

SENATE BILL 904 3
1 (E) (1) THE COUNTY BOARD SHALL SUBMIT A FORMAL PLAN OF
2 ASSISTANCE FOR ALL SCHOOL EMPLOYEES WHO WILL BE ADVERSELY AFFECTED BY
3 THE SERVICE CONTRACT.
4 (2) THE PLAN OF ASSISTANCE SHALL INCLUDE:
5 (I) EFFORTS TO PLACE AFFECTED EMPLOYEES IN VACANT
6 POSITIONS IN THE LOCAL SCHOOL SYSTEM;
7 (II) PROVISIONS IN THE SERVICE CONTRACT, IF FEASIBLE, FOR
8 THE HIRING BY THE CONTRACTOR OF DISPLACED EMPLOYEES; AND
9 (III) ADVANCE NOTIFICATION TO THE AFFECTED EMPLOYEES.
10 (F) (1) A SERVICE CONTRACT SHALL BE SUBJECT TO A DEPARTMENT
11 AUDIT TO DETERMINE COMPLIANCE WITH PROJECTED COST SAVINGS UNDER
12 SUBSECTION (D) OF THIS SECTION.
13 (2) AUDIT FINDINGS FROM AN AUDIT CONDUCTED IN ACCORDANCE
14 WITH PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION SHALL BE MADE AVAILABLE TO THE
15 PUBLIC.
16 6–133.
17 (A) (1) THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY FINDS THAT PARAEDUCATORS AND
18 OTHER EDUCATION SUPPORT PROFESSIONALS BENEFIT FROM IN–PERSON
19 TRAINING AS PART OF THE HIRING AND ONBOARDING PROCESS.
20 (2) IT IS THE INTENT OF THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY THAT IN–PERSON
21 TRAINING FOR PARAEDUCATORS AND OTHER EDUCATION SUPPORT
22 PROFESSIONALS BE EXPANDED IN PUBLIC SCHOOLS TO AT LEAST 2 DAYS OF
23 HIGH–QUALITY PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT DURING EACH SCHOOL YEAR.
24 (B) (1) SUBJECT TO PARAGRAPHS (2) AND (3) OF THIS SUBSECTION, ON
25 OR BEFORE JULY 1, 2027, THE DEPARTMENT SHALL DESIGN AND DEVELOP A NEW
26 SYSTEM OF PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT FOR PARAEDUCATORS AND OTHER
27 EDUCATION SUPPORT PROFESSIONALS THAT IS PAID AND OCCURS DURING
28 WEEKDAY SCHOOL HOURS.
29 (2) THE NEW SYSTEM OF PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT SHALL
30 INCLUDE:

4 SENATE BILL 904
1 (I) TRAINING TO FACILITATE PARAEDUCATORS AND
2 TEACHERS WORKING AS A TEAM TO IMPROVE STUDENT OUTCOMES;
3 (II) TRAINING FOR EDUCATION SUPPORT PROFESSIONALS ON
4 HOW TO:
5 1. COLLABORATE WITH TEACHERS AND
6 PARAEDUCATORS TO IMPROVE STUDENT PERFORMANCE AND BEHAVIOR;
7 2. IMPROVE STUDENT HEALTH AND SAFETY; AND
8 3. IMPROVE STUDENT LEARNING ENVIRONMENTS,
9 INCLUDING SCHOOL BUILDINGS, SCHOOL BUSES, PLAYGROUNDS, ATHLETIC FIELDS,
10 SCHOOL CAFETERIAS, AND SCHOOL HEALTH FACILITIES;
11 (III) TRAINING FOR PARAEDUCATORS ON SAFE PHYSICAL
12 RESTRAINT;
13 (IV) TRAINING FOR EDUCATION SUPPORT PROFESSIONALS ON
14 CRISIS PREVENTION AND DE–ESCALATION; AND
15 (V) JOB SKILLS TRAINING APPROPRIATE FOR SPECIFIC
16 EDUCATION SUPPORT PROFESSIONAL GROUPS.
17 (3) WHEN DESIGNING AND DEVELOPING THE SYSTEM OF
18 PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT REQUIRED UNDER THIS SUBSECTION, THE
19 DEPARTMENT SHALL CONSULT WITH COUNTY BOARDS AND NONPROFIT
20 ORGANIZATIONS WITH EXPERIENCE IN SUPPORTING EDUCATION SUPPORT
21 PROFESSIONALS, INCLUDING THE MARYLAND STATE EDUCATION ASSOCIATION.
22 (C) ON OR BEFORE JULY 1, 2027, THE DEPARTMENT SHALL ISSUE
23 GUIDANCE TO EACH COUNTY BOARD THAT DESCRIBES THE SYSTEM OF
24 PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT DEVELOPED AND DESIGNED UNDER THIS SECTION.
25 (D) ON OR BEFORE JUNE 30, 2028, EACH COUNTY BOARD SHALL PROVIDE
26 THE SYSTEM OF PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT DESIGNED BY THE DEPARTMENT
27 UNDER THIS SECTION TO EACH PARAEDUCATOR AND EDUCATION SUPPORT
28 PROFESSIONAL WHO IS EMPLOYED IN A PUBLIC SCHOOL IN THE COUNTY.
29 (E) THIS SECTION MAY NOT BE CONSTRUED TO DIMINISH THE OBLIGATION
30 OF A COUNTY BOARD TO COMPLY WITH A COLLECTIVE BARGAINING AGREEMENT OR
31 AN EMPLOYMENT BENEFIT PROGRAM THAT ESTABLISHES GREATER REQUIREMENTS
32 THAN IMPOSED UNDER THIS SECTION.

SENATE BILL 904 5
1 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
2 1, 2026.

